context: The <b8_0>United States<b8_0/> shares land borders with <a0_0>Canada (to the north) and <b4_0>Mexico<b4_0/> (to the south),<a0_0/> and a territorial water border with <a1_0>Russia<a1_0/> in the northwest, and two territorial water borders in the southeast between Florida and Cuba, and Florida and the Bahamas. The contiguous <a2_0>forty-eight<a2_0/> states are otherwise bounded by the Pacific Ocean on the west, the <b5_0>Atlantic Ocean<b5_0/> on the east, and the Gulf of Mexico to the southeast. <b6_0>Alaska<b6_0/> borders the <a3_0>Pacific Ocean<a3_0/> to the south, the Bering Strait to the west, and the Arctic Ocean to the north, while Hawaii lies far to the southwest of the mainland in the <b7_0>Pacific Ocean<b7_0/>.
